description:
&lt;p&gt;Powys Teaching Health Board are looking for an experienced Paediatric Clinical Lead Dietitian to take responsibility for North Powys caseload, and develop the service across the Powys providing clinical and professional leadership.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Dietetics service provides support for adults and children across Powys striving to deliver the best, most up-to-date evidence based care for patients within Public Health Strategic Framework for AHPs in Wales. You will be part of the Department leadership team working closely with colleagues, and reporting to the Professional Head to develop the community paediatric service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;PTHB Therapy Team are a forward thinking and innovative, and have recently embraced technology to support evolving health care needs resulting from the remote locality of Powys service users and Covid 19 pandemic. This has included use of digital records as part of WCCIS, and Attend Anywhere video consultations, which have proved successful and are well supported by Trust IT teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a clinician with a positive approach and a can-do attitude who is able to support and manage change. You should be able to work on your own initiative, but also contribute to Team goals and have good ability to multi-task and manage caseload. You will be the Paediatric Lead for the Department, and will support colleagues as needed in CAMHS and Eating Disorder service, and have awareness of legislative requirements eg ALNET. Ideally the post holder will have experience in staff and performance management, and would be working towards a Masters Level or similar qualification.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The service predominately operates from a number of sites across North Powys and you will be expected to travel to the different sites when required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable but not essential for this post; English and/or Welsh speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please contact Professional Head of Service, Penny Doyle, for an informal chat about this post on 01686 613245/ 07827 234314 or email penny.doyle@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
